[Student "W"]
{[showcards W:D5 E:DQ,D7,D3 S:D6,DT,DA,CQ]

You are North. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \D5, South wins the \DQ and returns the \D7. West holds up his \DA until the third round. He then plays the \CQ  

Play the \C8.

You assume (hope) that South holds the \CA. If he does then he will need help from you to decide which trick he should win. You play the \C8 first, and the \C2 next to show an even number.

If South is paying attention he will know to win the THIRD \C. This will kill dummy's \C suit, and with it West's chance of making 9 tricks.}
[Play "W"]D5

