[Student "E"]
{[showcards W:CA]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown. Partner led the \CA, dummy played the \C2 

Play the \C3.

If you signal with the \C9 East will continue with the \CK and another which you will have to ruff. You will give up your NATURAL trump trick by doing so. Worse, you will allow South's \CJ to be established as a winner that North can later discard a \D on. 

Much better to play low. Partner will surely switch to a \D, and North will probably finesse, though it doesn't matter whether he does or not. You will win the \DK, return the \C9 back to East's \CK, and still have your trump trick for later.}
[Play "W"]CA

